And those were conducted in patients -- moderate to severely ill patients suffering from atopic dermatitis in need of systemic treatment. And that's really where we believe Olumiant is bringing the biggest benefits to patients early on in the treatment paradigm while FDA currently has a position of saving Olumiant for the refractory patients, where we see the incremental value of Olumiant to be quite limited. And if that doesn't change, it's likely that we will receive a complete response letter. And if so, we will continue to focus our efforts on the very successful launches that we have seen outside of the U.S.

for atopic dermatitis, as well as a very strong rheumatoid arthritis franchise with -- as well as preparing for, hopefully, an approval of alopecia areata in the U.S. and other markets later on this year. Moving on to mirikizumab. Yes, we had recently the readout of LUCENT-2 just prior to the end of last year.

